=Activate or Reset the 3G Modem in the Cr-48= 

----
====Use this guide if you are not able to activate Verizon 3G Wireless or need to reset a previously activated 3G modem.==== 
====[[image:cr48verizon.jpg align="right"]]==== 
====Note: These steps must be completed within Chrome OS, not another operating system.==== 
====Before starting, you should try the [[http://www.google.com/support/chromeos/bin/static.py?page=ts.cs&ts=1257251|Google Internet connection troubleshooting guide.]]==== 
==== ==== 
==**Before you begin**== 
# ====Start your Cr-48 and sign in to Chrome OS==== 
# ====Press **ctrl + alt + t** to bring up a crosh prompt==== 
# ====Type <span style="background-color: #ffff00; font-family: 'Lucida Console',Monaco,monospace;">modem status</span> and press **enter**==== 
# ====The computer should respond with a page of information. You will need three numbers from this page:==== 
** **min** (this will be in the form of a phone number such as 3105551212)
** **mdn** (this will also be in the form of a phone number)
** **meid** (this will be a 14-digit code starting with the letter 'A'). This code can also be found under the Cr-48 battery
# ====If you contacted Verizon Wireless previously, when you call you will need to provide your security code or the name of your first pet==== 
<span style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.917969); color: #222222; display: block; font-family: arial,sans-serif;">
</span>
==<span style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.917969); color: #222222; font-family: arial,sans-serif;">**Change ownership or "reset" the Verizon 3G account on a previously activated Cr-48**</span>== 
====<span style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.917969); color: #222222; font-family: arial,sans-serif;">If you have a Cr-48 with a 3G account activated by the previous owner, this account will need to be deactivated before you can activate your own account.</span>==== 
<span style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.917969); color: #222222; display: block; font-family: arial,sans-serif;">
# ====Ask the previous owner to call Verizon Mobile Broadband support at (800) 766-8419 and take the following steps:==== 
** Press **#** to skip the phone number section
** Press **2** to select "no contract"
** Wait for a customer service representative
** Give them the **meid** of the Cr-48 (found in the process above as well as under the battery). DO NOT provide the min or mdn numbers -- deactivating these will not remove the account from the device.
** Ask them to deactivate the account
# ====Now you can go to the network icon on the bottom right of the screen (top right on Chrome OS versions prior to 20)==== 
# ====Select "Activate Verizon Wireless"==== 
# ====You should be presented with a screen to select a plan, or the free 100MB per month for 2 years==== 
</span>
==**3G Manual Activation and Modem Factory Reset**== 
# ====Call Verizon Mobile Broadband support at (800) 786-8419, get an agent on the line and provide them with your identifying information==== 
# ====Start your Cr-48 and sign in to Chrome OS==== 
# ====Press **ctrl + alt + t** to bring up a crosh prompt==== 
# ====Type <span style="background-color: #ffff00; font-family: 'Lucida Console',Monaco,monospace;">modem factory-reset</span> and press **enter**. The computer will respond with a prompt <span style="font-family: 'Lucida Console',Monaco,monospace;">spc [000000]:</span>==== 
# ====Type <span style="background-color: #ffff00; font-family: 'Lucida Console',Monaco,monospace;">000000</span> and press **enter**==== 
# ====If successful you will see a new prompt with no errors. Wait 60 seconds before proceeding to the next step==== 
# ====Type <span style="background-color: #ffff00; font-family: 'Lucida Console',Monaco,monospace;">modem status</span> and press **enter**==== 
# ====If the computer does not respond, wait 5-10 seconds and repeat step 7==== 
# ====The computer should respond with something similar to: <span style="font-family: 'Lucida Console',Monaco,monospace;">Modem /org/chromium/ModemManager/Gobi/0</span>==== 
# ====Verizon Wireless agent will provide you with the following numbers:==== 
** **min** (will be a phone number, ie. 3105551313)
** **mdn** (will be a phone number, ie. 3105551212)
** **spc** (can be 000000 by default)
** **system_id** (based on your home address or location)
# ====Type <span style="background-color: #ffff00; font-family: 'Lucida Console',Monaco,monospace;">modem activate-manual</span> and press **enter**. The computer will then prompt you to enter the **min**, **mdn**, **spc** and **system_id**. Press **enter** after entering each to bring the next prompt.==== 
# ====If successful, you will see a new prompt with no errors==== 
# ====Type <span style="background-color: #ffff00; font-family: 'Lucida Console',Monaco,monospace;">exit</span> and press **enter**==== 
# ====Restart your Cr-48 and sign in to Chrome OS==== 
# ====Click on the WiFi status bar (top right corner) and select Activate 3G wireless==== 
# ====Follow the prompts through the activation process. If you receive a 'Connection Error' see the troubleshooting steps below.==== 
# ====Once the activation process is complete, disable WiFi and verify your 3G connection by visiting a web site such as Google.com==== 
==== ==== 
==== ==== 
==Troubleshooting== 
====If you receive a 'Connection Error' during the activation process, take the following steps:==== 
# ====Click on the WiFi status bar (top right corner) and select Disable cellular==== 
# ====Power down the Cr-48 (hold down power button to shut down)==== 
# ====Reboot the Cr-48==== 
# ====Sign in to Chrome OS==== 
# ====Click on the WiFi status bar (top right corner) and select Disable WiFi==== 
# ====Click on the WiFi status bar and select Enable Cellular. Verizon should now be listed as ‘Connected’==== 
# ====Click on Network settings and select Options next to Verizon Wireless, and you can review the 'Connection Details' screen==== 
# ====Click the Close button and verify your connection by visiting a web site such as Google.com==== 

